	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f107294162160335>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=7&mid=107294162160335>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=7&mid=107294162160335>Battle Cleric</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=7&mid=107294162160335#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jan 1st 2:20 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=16271><span id= >TurboFreak</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok to all those that think Clerics should only sit on their behinds, heal the party and occasionally throw out a DD or stun: Shame on you! Cleric's can be VERY effective in melee and STILL be main healer for the group. I have been doing this effectively since I gained 55 with my first summoned hammer and Yaulp V.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since then it has become much easier and all groups I have joined are amazed at me being able to fight AND heal the party without going OOM or even running low. Granted you will find this easier with a KEI at 55 until you get the hang of things but at 58 with your Blessed Armor of the Risen spell up, Yaulp V going and all 3 levels of Mana Regen in AA you will not need to have a KEI to effectively Melee and Heal your party. Here is what I usually do in combat and have yet to run out of mana or lose a member to death.<br><br>1) I cast Mark of Karn (Lvl 56) on the Mob. This will allow the Melee'ers that are beating on it to be healed while doing so thus eliminating my need to heal frequently. Also negates the effects of Damage Shields on Mobs if they have one up as the Heal of the spell and the Damage of the DS on the Mob tend to cancel each other out in effect. &lt;This can be replaced with Mark of Retribution (Lvl 54) prior to reaching 56 as it will add slightly to your damage output. Not really useful if Mob is slowed&gt;<br><br>2) I will then cast Unswerving Hammer of Faith. In a 2 mob pull situation I will cast the Hammer on one mob and when it gets close to death I will pull off and switch targets. The Hammer will change targets once the first mob is dead and you will not need to recast thus saving mana.<br><br>3) Yaulp V....Cast it as soon as it pops up and keep it going even when not in combat. This spell gives you 10 mana per tick! You never need to sit unless you need to swap spells. Plus you get Dex to allow your hammer to Proc more often in battle. More damage output done the faster the mob falls. The faster the mob falls the LESS damage it can do and the less you have to heal.<br><br>4) Use Complete Heal on your Melee'ers when possible. Yes I know some do not like being at 60% and having the next pull come in but I do NOT pop a CH until the Main Tank is at 45-50% life. This saves you mana and will keep you up fighting. IF 50% of the group are sitting at 75 or 80% I will just use Word of Vigor on them to bring them close to if not all the way to full health. Usually the Mark of Karn will bring them to full life over the course of a few battles if they are not the MT.<br><br>So with everything I get the following Mana regen at Level 58 while standing:<br>Blessed Armor of the Risen  6 mana / tick<br>Yaulp V                    10 mana / tick<br>(AA)Mental Clarity 3        3 mana / tick<br>                    Total  19 mana / tick <br><br>Here is what I used at 55:<br>(AA)Mental Clarity 3        3 mana / tick<br>Yaulp V                    10 mana / tick<br>KEI (Lvl 60 Chanter spell) 16 mana / tick<br>                    Total  29 mana / tick<br><br>Therefore IF I got KEI at 58 I would throw more heals more often of the HoT variety when I have mana to burn and also pop a few DD spells at the mob. On top of all of this I am usually PAC assisting the Monk with the pulls so I have no time to sit. Our groups always kill mobs quickly and they are very happy to have the added damage I can bring. I have found though that with proper mana conservation a party will never be wanting for healing and the cleric will never run LoM or have to sit to med without KEI. I have been a devoted Battle Cleric since 55 and I can now NEVER go back to just sitting and healing in a group. I feel I am wasting my talent by doing that. <br> <br>   So all of you Clerics out there that are still sitting on your duffs at 55, you need to Stand up and show those around you what we can really do!!<br><br><br>Venerable Turvey Deathbane<br>Level 59 Battle Cleric<br>Firiona Vie server<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
