	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Dec 23rd 4:47 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=289270><span id= >Blanik</span></a><br><span id=notbold>11 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>i was just wondering is there anything usefull that a cleric can do besides heal? (DD,DoT,decent melee, ect). <br><br>Also i heard that you need to spend lots of extra cash on spell components. is this true? if so what types of spells do you need the extra stuff for?<br><br>thanks for the help : )<br><br><i><span class=sm>Edited, Tue Dec 23 19:56:42 2003 by Blanik</span class=sm></i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
