	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=223932><span id=Scholar>Aarenla</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>82 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.89]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Depends on what you want to do with your cleric really. When I made my cleric I planned on grouping primarily so I slammed all but 5 points into wis. If you want to have a battle cleric you might want to go with different stats. IMHO a cleric is a healer though, we are there to heal others. <br>One thing to remember is that almost everything on a cleric can be cheaply built on but wisdom. Wisdom gear runs pretty high. Stamina gear is right up there with wis but with the buffs we get it's never really been a major concern of mine.<br>Level five takes only a couple hours to get to so if you need to start over it's not that big a deal. If you aren't happy with your cleric now it's better to go ahead and start him over rather then get to level 40 and then decide you really can't take him any more.<br>On the other hand 103 wis is not that bad. In the early stages you are going to run out of manna easily and until you get med it takes forever to get manna back. I think my HIE cleric has base wis of 120 or so which isn't that much of a difference but add gear and it's over 255.</p>&nbsp;<br>Of his knowledge a man should never boast,<br>Rather be sparing of speach<br>When to his house a wiser comes:<br>Seldom do those who are silent make mistakes;<br>Mother wit is ever a faithful freind.</td></tr>
